This file is a learning plan designed for junior engineers to learn about and develop skills in building agentic AI systems, specifically focusing on large language models (LLMs) and their practical applications. It covers foundational knowledge of LLMs, prompt engineering techniques, and the integration of tools into AI agents. The content includes detailed weekly plans, study materials, hands-on coding exercises, and common pitfalls to avoid, all aimed at helping engineers transition from basic understanding to confident design and implementation of agentic AI systems.